Subject to compliance with this Agreement, the user may use the Tool for personal, commercial, and business purposes.
The user may copy, back up, and modify the Tool on devices owned, possessed, or managed by the user.
However, the user may not provide the Tool to any third party in a form from which the Tool can be extracted.

Article 3. Prohibited Conduct
The user must not engage in any of the following:

1. Redistributing, transferring, selling, reselling, lending, renting, or sharing the Tool
2. Distributing any data that contains all or part of the Tool, even if modified
3. Selling the Tool as the primary product
4. Decompiling, disassembling, reverse engineering, or otherwise analyzing the Tool when obfuscation has been applied
5. Misrepresenting oneself as the developer, Rights Holder, or seller
6. Making any representation or advertisement that may cause others to mistakenly believe that the user is an official provider of, or affiliated with, the Tool
7. Using the Tool in a manner that infringes the rights of any third party
8. Using the Tool in violation of laws, regulations, public order, or morality
9. Engaging in any conduct that violates this Agreement

Article 4. Disclaimer of Warranties
The Tool is provided “as is.”
The Rights Holder makes no warranty regarding the completeness, accuracy, usefulness, safety, fitness for a particular purpose, or continuous operation of the Tool.
The Rights Holder also does not warrant operation in every environment, compatibility with external software, external services, or other products, or the absence of defects.

Article 5. Limitation of Liability
The user shall use the Tool at the user’s own risk.
The Rights Holder shall bear no liability for any damage arising from the use, modification, installation, update, deletion, inability to use, or malfunction of the Tool.
Such damage includes data corruption, loss of work, loss of profits, loss of opportunities, disputes with third parties, and any other direct or indirect damage.

Article 6. Backups
Before using the Tool, the user shall back up all necessary data, projects, settings, and files.

Article 7. Support
The Rights Holder has no obligation to provide repairs, maintenance, updates, responses to inquiries, or any other support for the Tool.

Article 8. Termination
If the user violates this Agreement, the Rights Holder may terminate this Agreement without prior notice.
In such a case, the user shall immediately cease using the Tool and shall endeavor to delete the Tool and all copies in the user’s possession.
The provisions concerning ownership of rights, prohibited conduct, disclaimer of warranties, and limitation of liability shall survive termination of this Agreement.

Article 9. Amendments
